# Staging preview & Apple HIG (after each relevant change)

## When this applies

Whenever you **edit** portfolio **UI or UX** (`*.html`, `css/main.css`, `js/main.js`, assets that affect layout or branding).

## 1. Real-time / local staging

- Tell the user to preview at **`http://127.0.0.1:8765`** (or `http://localhost:8765`).
- If no server is obviously running, give the exact command from **`docs/staging.md`**:
  `cd /Users/mojtabatorabi/Desktop/Portfolio && python3 -m http.server 8765`
- Remind them to **hard-refresh** after changes (e.g. Cmd+Shift+R) if styles look stale.

## 2. Human Interface Guidelines

- Treat **[Apple Human Interface Guidelines](https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines)** as the bar for spacing, typography, touch targets, motion, accessibility, and platform patterns.
- Before considering UI work “done,” cross-check against **`docs/hig-checklist.md`** in this repo (8pt rhythm, safe areas, contrast, 44pt targets, reduced motion, theme behavior).
- If something can’t meet HIG fully (e.g. static hosting limits), note the tradeoff briefly for the user.

## 3. Git

- Do **not** auto-push after every edit unless the user explicitly asks to push. Prefer: staging + HIG pass → user approval → then commit/push per **`portfolio-workflow.mdc`** when requested.
